title: Rituraj Singh Death News: TV actor Rituraj Singh passes away due to cardiac arrest at the age of 59; Close friend Amit Behl confirms it | - Times of India
meta_description: TV actor Rituraj Singh passes away due to cardiac arrest at the age of 59. Close friend Amit Behl confirms the sad news. Read more about the sudden demise of the talented actor.
main_content: Sign In TOI News tv hindi TV actor Rituraj Singh passes away due to cardiac arrest at the age of 59; Close friend Amit Behl confirms it Trending Ankita Lokhande Prachi Bansal Dilip Joshi Bigg Boss Kannada 11 Palak Sindhwani Mithil Jain Anjali Tatrari Ankita Lokhande Prachi Bansal Dilip Joshi Bigg Boss Kannada 11 Palak Sindhwani Mithil Jain Anjali Tatrari Ankita Lokhande Prachi Bansal Dilip Joshi Bigg Boss Kannada 11 Palak Sindhwani Mithil Jain Anjali Tatrari This story is from February 20, 2024 TV actor Rituraj Singh passes away due to cardiac arrest at the age of 59; Close friend Amit Behl confirms it etimes.in / Updated: Feb 20, 2024, 11:29 IST Share AA + Text Size Small Medium Large Follow us Rituraj Singh passed away last night due to cardiac arrest. The actor was only 59. Rituraj Singh , who has impressed fans with many of his amazing roles in the industry over the years passed away last night due to cardiac arrest . The actor was only 59 and was dealing with issues related to his pancreas. The news has come out as a big shock to his close ones and the fans. Actor Rituraj who was suffering from some pancreatic disease and was hospitalised recently passed away due to cardiac arrest. Netizens and close ones has mourned to his sudden demise and sent condolences to his family. Amit Behl , who was good friends with him confirmed the news and expressed his grief over the same. He said, "Yes he passed away due to cardiac arrest. He was admitted to a hospital some time back for treatment of pancreas returned home had some cardiac complications and passed away." The actor was last seen in TV show Anupamaa, where he played the role of Yashpal Singh, a cafe owner. Anupamaa played by Rupali Ganguly worked at the cafe and was often seen sharing screen with the late-actor. Fans quite liked his work in the show and were impressed with the same. Yashpal was an important character in the show, especially since Anuj and Anupamaa parted ways. The cafe was shown in America, where Anupmaa works for Yashpal and is quite known for its delicacies. He was an Indian television actor worked prominently with Bollywood. He has played different roles in a number of Indian TV shows like Banegi Apni Baat aired on Zee TV in 1993, Jyoti, Hitler Didi, Shapath, Warrior High, Aahat, Adaalat, and Diya Aur Baati Hum.
